results.deck: Traveller's Tales is a video game company responsible for making video game adaptations from existing franchises (films etc.)
results.description: Traveller's Tales was founded in in 1989 in the United Kingdom by Jon Burton. The company released their first game, Leander, in 1991 and went on to produce mainly platformers and jump and run games such as Pugsy and Mickey Mania. In 2004, Travellerâ€™s Tales merged with publisher Giant Interactive Entertainment to form TT Games. Their most recent output has been focussing on creating games based on existing franchises (for companies such as Disney etc.) - notable games include A Bug's Life, the LEGO games series and more.
